<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - REMOVE AND INSTALL - COMPLETE CLUSTER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COMPLETE CLUSTER</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0803401">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Protect the bezel during removal by placing a soft cloth on the forward side of the
                    steering column.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the the two cluster mounting screws located on the lower front face of the
                    cluster,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803402" appearance="hottext">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803402" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803402" filename="../figg08/G0803402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Removing Instrument Cluster</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PAN HEAD SCREWS (8-18 X 2-1/4")</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. INSTRUMENT CLUSTER BEZEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CLUSTER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. WIRING HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. INSTRUMENT PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. RELEASE TABS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Depress the two gray retaining tabs located on the top corners of the bezel .</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Holding the tabs depressed, pull the cluster forward and gently release it from the
                    frame. If the cluster does not come loose easily, put more pressure on the tabs and continue to pull
                    gently. Do not attempt to pry the cluster from the frame as damage will result.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the three wiring harness connectors from the back of the cluster assembly,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803403">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803403" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803403" filename="../figg08/G0803403.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Instrument Cluster Wiring Harness Connections</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the fitting on the back of the oil pressure gauge,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803404">Figure 4</hotlnk>. The oil gauge elbow must be held with a wrench while
                    disconnecting the oil line.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803404" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803404" filename="../figg08/G0803404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Removing Oil Line</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CLUSTER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. OIL GAUGE FITTING</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. OIL LINE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>When removing or in stalling oil pressure gauges, be sure to use two wrenches to remove or
                            in stall the tubing on the rear of the gauge. One wrench must be on the elbow to prevent it
                            from turning.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After bleeding the air system, disconnect the air lines from the fittings on the back of
                    the air gauge. A double needle air pressure gauge is used with vehicles with air brakes,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0803405">Figure 5</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0803405" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0803405" filename="../figg08/G0803405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Dual Air Gauge Connections</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Note the color of the air lines being removed from the gauge. The green line is for the
                            primary system and the orange line is for the secondary system.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The instrument cluster assembly is now free to be removed from the instrument panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the air lines to the air pressure gauge. The green line is for the primary
                    system and the orange for the secondary system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the oil line to the oil pressure gauge. Use two wrenches, making sure to hold
                    the oil line elbow firmly.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not exceed 36 lb. in. (4.0 N&#8226; m) of torque when tightening the air and oil
                            lines.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the three wiring harness connectors to the back of the cluster. These connectors
                    are color-coded for proper orientation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the cluster in the instrument panel frame and push the cluster gently until the
                    retaining tabs snap into place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the two cluster mounting screws on the lower front face of the cluster.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
